This paper deals with problems related to graph theory, specifically the concept of dominating induced matching. The paper discusses algorithms for finding minimum weighted dominating induced matching and counting the number of dominating induced matchings, which are topics that fall under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper involves algorithms and computational complexity, which are relevant to the categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Graph Theory (cs.GT), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
